ce:section.ce:para:

Figure 2a presents a TEM image of the iNGO-QDs and the inset shows the histogram of the size distribution. The size of the iNGO-QDs ranges from 2 to 6nm and is monodispersed at approximately 4nm. This high resolution TEM image (Figure 2b) presents the graphene {
   1

      1
      ¯

   00
} planes that have an inherent spacing distance of 0.213nm [20]. Selected area electron nanobeam diffraction patterns, projected perpendicularly onto the basal plane of an iNGO-QD particle (Figure 2c), revealed diffraction spots in a hexagonal arrangement identical to that of graphite projected in the [0001] direction. The TEM images and diffraction patterns demonstrate that these QDs are single crystals with a graphitic framework. Figure 2d presents an atomic force microscopy image of the iNGO-QDs on a mica substrate. The topographic heights were 0.8–2nm, indicating that the iNGO-QDs primarily consisted of between one and three layers of graphene sheets [22].
